transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah. I talked to, um, who did I talk to yesterday? Um, the, uh, Leo.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I was telling the man I ordered the taxes, and, um, I never received it.

Speaker 1: And I called, um, the post office.

Speaker 2: They don't got it, but I gave them the, um, the tracking number.

Speaker 1: They said, oh, no, we deliver that on February the 7th.

Speaker 2: I said, there ain't no taxes come on February the 7th.

Speaker 1: I got cameras out there in the front, so I didn't see them delivering that.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's your name and zip code, sir, so I can better help you?

Speaker 1: Oh, yeah. Sylvester Thompson. Zip code is 20110.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: One second.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: There we go.

Speaker 2: 944 Taney Road.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay. So I'm just going to get it reshipped for you.

Speaker 1: I'm going to do a priority shipping on it, so it'll go a little bit faster for you, okay?

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. That'll work.

Speaker 1: All right. Thanks, sir.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
